        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7787_p1"> <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_7787_c0">Nachträglicher Stempel oben rechts mit von dritter Hand eingetragener Nummer: <orig>Gotthardbahn | <date when="1872-07-23">23 JULI 1872</date> | <choice><abbr>N<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr><expan>Numero (Nummer)</expan></choice> 2134.</orig> – 
              Nachträgliche Inhaltsangabe oben links von dritter Hand: <orig>Gesuch des Herrn Fr. Beaumont | in <placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName> um Beantwortung | seines Schreibens vom <date when="1872-07-08">8 Juli 1872</date>. | I. <choice><abbr>Depart.</abbr><expan>Departement</expan></choice> </orig> – Nachträgliche Notiz unten rechts von dritter Hand: <orig><choice><abbr>Prot.</abbr><expan>Protokoll</expan></choice> <date when="1872-07-24">24. <hi>VII.</hi> 72</date>. <choice><abbr>N.</abbr><expan>Nummer</expan></choice> 586.</orig> </note> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <hi rend="printed">THE MACHINE TUNNELLING COMPANY, LIMITED.</hi>
          <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
          <hi rend="printed">2. Westminster Chambers, <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>Victoria Street, <choice><abbr>S.W.</abbr><expan>SouthWest (Südwesten)</expan></choice> </hi>
        </p>
      
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7787_p2"><lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>
          <hi rend="printed">
            <placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName>
          </hi>
          <date when="1872-07-20">July 20 <hi rend="printed">187</hi>2</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7787_p3"><lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
          <choice><abbr>Mons<hi rend="sup">r</hi> </abbr><expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan></choice> A, E. Escher
          <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>[<choice><abbr>etc.</abbr><expan>et cetera (und anderes)</expan></choice>][<choice><abbr>etc.</abbr><expan>et cetera (und anderes)</expan></choice>][<choice><abbr>etc.</abbr><expan>et cetera (und anderes)</expan></choice>]<note type="transcript">wohl das sog. tironische Et und c. als Zeichen für etc.</note> </p>
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7787_p4"><lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
          <placeName key="Zürich (Stadt)">Zurich</placeName>,</p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7787_p5"><lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>Sir,</p>
      </div>
    </front><body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7787_p6"><lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>May I beg of you to write me a reply to my
       <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>letter of the <date when="1872-07-08">8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> July</date>, asking for certain information
       <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>necessary to submit my offer for the <placeName key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">Saint Gothard</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>contract in the form you wish. –</p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7787_p7"><lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>I am somewhat at a loss to understand
       <lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>this delay as you have so often impressed me
       <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>with the necessity that existed for losing no 
       <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>time: – I beg to point out to you the absolute
       <lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>necessity there is to get the question of the Contract
       <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>decided at once, or it will be too late to do any<lb xml:id="p1-l19" break="no"/>thing on the mountain this season and
       <lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>another year will be lost.</p>
    </body><back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7787_p8"><lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>I have the honor to be
        <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/>Sir
        <lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>Your obedient <choice><abbr>Serv<hi rend="sup">t</hi> </abbr><expan>Servant (Diener)</expan></choice></p>
      </div>
      <div type="signature">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7787_p9"><lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>Fred Beaumont.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>Chairman of <choice><abbr>M. T. Co<hi rend="sup">y</hi> </abbr><expan>Mountain Tunnel Company</expan></choice></p> </div>
    </back></text></TEI>